<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for-loop initializes and updates two objects: it sets j and io in the first clause and performs j++ and io++ in the third clause. MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 requires the third clause to modify only the loop counter (and there must be only one loop counter). Incrementing io (a second iterator/pointer) in the third clause therefore violates Clause 3 (and effectively introduces a second loop counter), so the rule is violated.
</scenario>

